# CHUNK 2: Load Factbook CSV
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

factbook_raw <- read_tsv(
  "Enrollment Table_data.csv",
  locale = locale(encoding = "UTF-16"),
  show_col_types = FALSE
)

# Clean: extract year, rename columns
factbook <- factbook_raw %>%
  rename(
    level     = Level,
    term      = `FB Term`,
    headcount = `HC Label`
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    year      = as.integer(str_extract(term, "\\d{4}")),
    headcount = as.integer(headcount)
  ) %>%
  select(level, year, headcount) %>%
  filter(!is.na(headcount))

# Total SHRS headcount per year
factbook_total <- factbook %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarise(total = sum(headcount, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop")

# CHUNK 4: Map to 9 Focus Programs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

program_map <- tribble(
  ~program_label,  ~program_pattern,
  "AT",        "Athletic Training \\(AT-",
  "AuD",       "Audiology \\(AUDIO-AUD\\)",
  "DN",        "Nutrition and Dietetics \\(ND-MS\\)",
  "DPT",       "Physical Therapy \\(PT-DPT\\)",
  "HIM",       "Health Informatics \\(HI-MS\\)",
  "OTD",       "Occupational Therapy \\(OT-OTD\\)",
  "OT_CScD",   "Occupational Therapy \\(OT-CSD\\)",
  "PA_Hybrid", "Physician Assistant Studies \\(PAS-MS\\) - Hybrid",
  "SLP",       "Comm Science and Disorders \\(CSD-MA\\) - SLP"
)

ay_cols <- c("AY21","AY22","AY23","AY24","AY25",
             "AY26","AY27","AY28","AY29","AY30")

# For each program label, find matching rows and sum them
programs_long <- map_dfr(seq_len(nrow(program_map)), function(i) {
  label   <- program_map$program_label[i]
  pattern <- program_map$program_pattern[i]

  program_raw %>%
    filter(str_detect(program_raw, regex(pattern, ignore_case = TRUE))) %>%
    summarise(across(all_of(ay_cols), ~ sum(.x, na.rm = TRUE))) %>%
    mutate(program = label)
}) %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols      = all_of(ay_cols),
    names_to  = "ay_label",
    values_to = "enrollment"
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    year         = as.integer(paste0("20", str_remove(ay_label, "AY"))),
    is_projected = year >= 2026
  )

# Verify  AY25 actuals for all 9 programs
programs_long %>%
  filter(year == 2025) %>%
  select(program, enrollment) %>%
  arrange(desc(enrollment)) %>%
  print()

# CHUNK 6: Linear Regression Forecast (AY21AY25  AY26AY30)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Fits a separate lm() per program on actuals, then predicts forward.
# Also extracts R-squared and p-value so you can see how well
# the trend fits each program.

actuals <- programs_long %>% filter(!is_projected)

# --- 6A: Fit a linear model per program ---
model_fits <- actuals %>%
  group_by(program) %>%
  group_map(~ {
    mod <- lm(enrollment ~ year, data = .x)
    tibble(
      program   = .y$program,
      r_squared = summary(mod)$r.squared,
      p_value   = summary(mod)$coefficients[2, 4],  # p-value for year slope
      slope     = coef(mod)[["year"]],               # students gained per year
      intercept = coef(mod)[["(Intercept)"]]
    )
  }) %>%
  bind_rows()

# Print model diagnostics
cat("=== Linear Regression Model Fit per Program ===\n")
## === Linear Regression Model Fit per Program ===
model_fits %>%
  mutate(
    r_squared = round(r_squared, 3),
    p_value   = round(p_value, 4),
    slope     = round(slope, 1),
    fit       = case_when(
      r_squared >= 0.85 ~ "Strong",
      r_squared >= 0.60 ~ "Moderate",
      TRUE              ~ "Weak"
    )
  ) %>%
  arrange(desc(r_squared)) %>%
  print()

# CHUNK 6 REVISED: Two-Step Forecast
# Step 1: Forecast total SHRS enrollment using 10-year factbook trend
# Step 2: Forecast each program's % share, then multiply by projected total
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

# --- STEP 1: Forecast total SHRS enrollment (20262030) ---
# Use all 10 years of factbook data for the school-wide lm()

total_model <- lm(total ~ year, data = factbook_total)

cat("=== Step 1: School-Wide Total Enrollment Model ===\n")
## === Step 1: School-Wide Total Enrollment Model ===
cat("R-squared:", round(summary(total_model)$r.squared, 3), "\n")
## R-squared: 0.922
cat("P-value:  ", round(summary(total_model)$coefficients[2,4], 4), "\n")
## P-value:   0
cat("Slope:    +", round(coef(total_model)[["year"]], 1), "students/year\n\n")
## Slope:    + 91.3 students/year
# Predict total enrollment AY26AY30
total_forecast <- tibble(year = 2026:2030) %>%
  mutate(
    total        = round(predict(total_model, newdata = .)),
    source       = "LM Forecast"
  )

# --- STEP 3: Fit lm() on each program's SHARE over time ---
share_models <- program_shares %>%
  group_by(program) %>%
  group_map(~ {
    mod <- lm(share ~ year, data = .x)
    tibble(
      program   = .y$program,
      r_squared = round(summary(mod)$r.squared, 3),
      p_value   = round(summary(mod)$coefficients[2, 4], 4),
      slope     = coef(mod)[["year"]],
      intercept = coef(mod)[["(Intercept)"]]
    )
  }) %>%
  bind_rows()

cat("\n=== Step 2: Share Model Fit per Program ===\n")
## 
## === Step 2: Share Model Fit per Program ===
share_models %>%
  mutate(
    fit = case_when(
      r_squared >= 0.85 ~ "Strong",
      r_squared >= 0.60 ~ "Moderate",
      TRUE              ~ "Weak"
    )
  ) %>%
  arrange(desc(r_squared)) %>%
  print()

# --- STEP 4: Project shares forward, multiply by total forecast ---
share_forecast <- share_models %>%
  crossing(year = 2026:2030) %>%
  mutate(
    projected_share = intercept + slope * year,
    # Floor at 0, cap at reasonable max
    projected_share = pmax(projected_share, 0)
  ) %>%
  left_join(total_forecast %>% select(year, total), by = "year") %>%
  mutate(
    enrollment   = round(projected_share * total),
    is_projected = TRUE,
    source       = "LM Forecast"
  ) %>%
  select(program, year, enrollment, projected_share, total, is_projected, source)

cat("\n=== Final Program Enrollment Forecast (AY26AY30) ===\n")

# TUITION CHUNK 2 FIXED
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

t_cols_actual <- c("T_AY21","T_AY22","T_AY23","T_AY24","T_AY25")

# Map tuition to 9 programs
tuition_9prog <- map_dfr(seq_len(nrow(program_map)), function(i) {
  label   <- program_map$program_label[i]
  pattern <- program_map$program_pattern[i]

  tuition_raw %>%
    filter(str_detect(program_raw, regex(pattern, ignore_case = TRUE))) %>%
    summarise(across(all_of(t_cols_actual), ~ sum(.x, na.rm = TRUE))) %>%
    mutate(program = label)
}) %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols      = all_of(t_cols_actual),
    names_to  = "ay_label",
    values_to = "tuition"
  ) %>%
  mutate(year = as.integer(paste0("20", str_remove(ay_label, "T_AY"))))

# Join with enrollment for revenue per student
rev_per_student <- tuition_9prog %>%
  left_join(
    actuals %>% select(program, year, enrollment),
    by = c("program", "year")
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    rev_per_student = ifelse(enrollment > 0, tuition / enrollment, NA)
  )

# Tuition by program AY25  arrange BEFORE mutate
cat("=== Tuition by Program AY25 ===\n")

  filter(year == 2025) %>%
  arrange(desc(tuition)) %>%
  mutate(tuition_fmt = scales::dollar(tuition)) %>%
  select(program, tuition_fmt) %>%
  print()

# --- Chart T1: Total Tuition Revenue by Program (AY21AY25) ---

p_t1 <- tuition_9prog %>%
  mutate(tuition_M = tuition / 1e6) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = tuition_M,
             color = program, group = program)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 1.1) +
  geom_point(size = 2.5) +
  geom_label_repel(
    data = tuition_9prog %>%
      filter(year == 2025) %>%
      mutate(tuition_M = tuition / 1e6) %>%
      arrange(desc(tuition)),
    aes(label = paste0(program, "\n$",
                       round(tuition_M, 1), "M")),
    size          = 2.8,
    nudge_x       = 0.4,
    direction     = "y",
    segment.size  = 0.3,
    box.padding   = 0.3,
    label.padding = 0.15,
    label.size    = 0.2,
    show.legend   = FALSE
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(values = program_colors) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = 2021:2025,
    labels = paste0("AY", 21:25),
    expand = expansion(add = c(0.2, 1.5))
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    labels = scales::dollar_format(suffix = "M"),
    expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1))
  ) +
  labs(
    title    = "Gross Tuition Revenue by Program (AY21AY25)",
    subtitle = "9 focus programs  actual gross tuition",
    x        = "Academic Year",
    y        = "Gross Tuition Revenue",
    color    = NULL,
    caption  = "University of Pittsburgh  School of Health and Rehabilitation Sciences"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 12) +
  theme(
    plot.title       = element_text(face = "bold", size = 13),
    plot.subtitle    = element_text(size = 9, color = "#555555"),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    legend.position  = "right"
  )

print(p_t1)

# --- Chart T3: Enrollment Share vs Revenue Share (bubble) ---
# Shows which programs punch above/below their weight

share_comparison <- rev_per_student %>%
  filter(year == 2025) %>%
  mutate(
    enroll_share  = enrollment / sum(enrollment, na.rm = TRUE),
    revenue_share = tuition / sum(tuition, na.rm = TRUE),
    efficiency    = revenue_share / enroll_share
  )

p_t3 <- share_comparison %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = enroll_share, y = revenue_share,
             color = program, size = tuition)) +
  # Reference line: equal share
  geom_abline(slope = 1, intercept = 0,
              linetype = "dashed", color = "#AABBCC") +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.85) +
  geom_label_repel(
    aes(label = program),
    size          = 3,
    box.padding   = 0.4,
    segment.size  = 0.3,
    show.legend   = FALSE
  ) +
  annotate("text", x = 0.28, y = 0.22,
           label = " Below weight\n(more enrollment, less revenue)",
           size = 2.8, color = "#888888", fontface = "italic",
           hjust = 0) +
  annotate("text", x = 0.02, y = 0.38,
           label = "Above weight \n(less enrollment, more revenue)",
           size = 2.8, color = "#888888", fontface = "italic",
           hjust = 0) +
  scale_color_manual(values = program_colors, guide = "none") +
  scale_size_continuous(
    range  = c(4, 14),
    labels = scales::dollar_format(),
    name   = "Total Revenue"
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +
  labs(
    title    = "Enrollment Share vs Revenue Share (AY25)",
    subtitle = "Points above dashed line generate more revenue than their enrollment share suggests",
    x        = "Share of 9-Program Enrollment",
    y        = "Share of 9-Program Revenue",
    caption  = "Bubble size = total gross tuition revenue"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 12) +
  theme(
    plot.title       = element_text(face = "bold", size = 13),
    plot.subtitle    = element_text(size = 9, color = "#555555"),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    legend.position  = "right"
  )

print(p_t3)
